cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.IT. 

The paper proposes a novel semidefinite relaxation formulation for maximum a posteriori (MAP) inference over discrete Markov random fields, which is a fundamental task in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the scalability of the proposed method, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
